Title: Andrews Ecoflo gas control valve White
Description: A genuine Andrews spare, this gas control valve, in white, is compatible with Andrews RSC 150, RSC 190, 24/39, 32/40, 40/61, 63/62 and 84/87. The gas valve is employed in the distribution of gas. When gas is required in the burner the printed circuit board (PCB) sends a signal to the gas valve, which opens to allow gas to flow into the burner or the pilot assembly (depending on the model of the appliance).

Title: Andrews MAXXflo flue box blanking plug
Description: This Andrews blanking plug is a part designed for the flue of MAXXflo boilers.  A boiler flue is the outlet through which steam and toxic gases resulting from the boiler's normal operation are safely expelled. Different models of flue are chosen to suit the type and location of the appliance. Title: Andrews spares ionisation electrode
Description: An Andrews brand spare, this ionisation electrode is compatible with SUPAflo R300, R600 and SF60 boilers.  An ignition (spark) electrode causes the spark that begins combustion within the burner while flame sensing electrodes are responsible for checking if there is a flame present in the burner to make sure that the boiler doesn't keep supplying gas without a flame. Title: Potterton 8801157 pilot assembly
Description: This Potterton 8801157 pilot assembly is a replacement part for the now defunct Potterton Commercial Derwent Prestige. A pilot assembly normally includes a pilot bracket, injector, electrode and thermocouple. The pilot flame ignites gas entering the boiler's main burner via the gas valve when the system is switched on. The pilot flame operates alongside the printed circuit board (PCB) and the rest of the pilot assembly for safe and efficient ignition.
